# Cursor Rules Maintenance

- `.cursor/rules/` is the only project-level Cursor rule system in this repo. Do not reintroduce legacy `.cursorrules`.
- Keep rules small, focused, and non-overlapping. Prefer one concern per rule and use file scoping instead of growing always-apply files.
- Keep always-apply rules for durable invariants and decision hierarchy only.
- Use file-scoped rules for local constraints.
- When architecture changes, update or delete outdated rules in the same task.
- If two rules say the same thing, merge or simplify them.
- Do not keep stale Cursor guidance as historical baggage. Rules should describe the current preferred path only.
